# List Pages Convention

All pages that display a list/table of records **must** use the `ListTable` component from `@/components/common/ListTable`. This enforces:

1. **ID column first** – Database ID (`row.id`) always appears as the first data column
2. **Consistent styling** – Shared table layout, loading, and empty states

## Usage

```jsx
import ListTable from "../components/common/ListTable";

<ListTable
  data={data?.data ?? []}
  loading={loading}
  page={page}
  limit={data?.meta?.limit ?? 20}
  emptyMessage="No items."
  columns={[
    { key: "name", label: "Name", render: (row) => row.name },
    { key: "status", label: "Status", render: (row) => <Badge>{row.status}</Badge> },
    { key: "actions", label: "Actions", align: "right", render: (row) => <Button>Edit</Button> },
  ]}
/>
```

## Optional: Selectable Rows

```jsx
<ListTable
  data={...}
  selectable
  selectedIds={selectedIds}
  onSelect={toggleSelect}
  onSelectAll={toggleSelectAll}
  allSelected={allSelected}
  getCheckboxLabel={(row) => `Select ${row.name}`}
  columns={[...]}
/>
```

## Don't

- Manually build table markup with `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>` for list data
- Add an ID column as a custom column in `columns` – it is added automatically
